<p>I have an XML file with subelements of elements:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;Root&gt;      &lt;Location&gt;          &lt;DepartureBoundary&gt;             &lt;DepartureBoundaryRadius&gt;600&lt;/DepartureBoundaryRadius&gt;          &lt;/DepartureBoundary&gt;      &lt;/Location&gt;      &lt;Location&gt;          &lt;DepartureBoundary&gt;             &lt;DepartureBoundaryRadius&gt;600&lt;/DepartureBoundaryRadius&gt;          &lt;/DepartureBoundary&gt;      &lt;/Location&gt; &lt;/Root&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Currently, I am doing the following to access the value for DepartureBoundaryRadius:</p>  <pre><code>XDocument locationsDoc = XDocument.Load("file.xml"); DepartureLocationBoundaryRadius = null; List&lt;DepartureBoundaryRadius&gt; radiusList = new List&lt;DepartureBoundaryRadius&gt;();  foreach (XElement locationElement in locationsDoc.Descendants("Root")) {     foreach (XElement locationSubElement in locationsDoc.Descendants("Location"))     {         foreach (XElement departureElement in locationsDoc.Descendants("DepartureBoundary"))         {              DepartureLocationBoundaryRadius =  departureElement.Element("DepartureRadius").Value));              radiusList.Add(DepartureLocationBoundaryRadius);         }     } } </code></pre>  <p>Is there an easier way to do this? I would rather assign the value of   DepartureLocationBoundaryRadius in one line or one statement -- especially since each Location has only one DepartureBoundaryRadius value. Any thoughts? Thanks!</p>